(`).  If there is a word on either side of the (`), he says it violates the VI naming policy...<br>
<br>
Quote from EQ naming policy page:<br>
<br>
Surnames may contain an accent ( ` ) provided one of the divisions of the name is not a word, it does not create a title or a sentence, or breaks up a real word. This accent is the only non-alpha character that is allowed in surnames. <br>
<br>
This is a very badly written policy.  It can be interpreted 2 different ways.  Ie the name cannot contain any words or the name can contain one but not two words.  <br>
<br>
But the /rude was because he was a dick about it.<br>
<br>
So beware anyone with a (`) and something that resembles a word because you will be nerfed.<br>
<br>
Gathea<br>
