<br>
I, for one, would wish that they would *really* tighten the rules and tighten enforcement of the naming policy.<br>
<br>
&quot;Buggers Alotasheep&quot; doesn't belong in the game.  After about a half-hour of seing that name running across my screen, I petitioned it.<br>
<br>
But Gaetha, after reading your excerpt about using the accent mark in a surname, I disagree, and only see one way to interpret that.<br>
<br>
The part you stated<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Surnames may contain an accent ( ` ) provided one of the divisions of the name is not a word,<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
clearly states to me that you cannot use the accent mark to break up a word like Ta'ble (as in table), but it also can't be used if EITHER side of the accent mark make a word in and of itself, such as Dip'ing (dip is a word, and there for disqualified).<br>
<br>
To me, the policy as you quoted it is pretty clear.<br>
<br>
